</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-D3B3AA3C-642B-43EB-9760-CE8F28515933"><title class="- topic/title ">Chiller location in the engine is marked in yellow</title></fig><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-FBE72DE8-E1D4-47B2-908D-056B7DFF553D"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-4EC8617B-E57A-4A26-BE83-ABADA86A1ECE-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-4EC8617B-E57A-4A26-BE83-ABADA86A1ECE-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-C624F5CF-9018-4D16-BE83-F3DBAA9E9071" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional overview</title><fig id="GUID-76BEC2CA-2B84-4511-9208-3DC392A10E46" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-17730902-14D0-4FD8-A105-D106402A5E1A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-17730902-14D0-4FD8-A105-D106402A5E1A-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Schematic chiller liquid flow. 
</b> 
</p><fig id="GUID-E09374F6-3034-4A62-8CBE-CFE57F0A6A96" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-A978A271-00C1-4385-967A-3F92103ACC37-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A978A271-00C1-4385-967A-3F92103ACC37-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Componant location on top of the chiller. 
</b> 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Chiller unit (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Teyu Chiller</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 06CH1 </compcodenr></comp>) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Control valve (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Control valve </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06Y1</compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">VALVE_CONTROL</compsignal></comp>) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Bypass valve (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Bypass valve </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06Y2</compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">VALVE_BYPASS</compsignal></comp>) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Heater (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Chiller heater 1</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06E1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">SSR_OUT1</compsignal></comp> / <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Chiller heater 2</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06E2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">SSR_OUT2</compsignal></comp>06E2) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pump (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Chiller pump motor </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06M1</compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CHIL_PUMP_Mo</compsignal></comp>) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> NTC (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Chiller NTC </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06R1</compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">NTC1</compsignal></comp>) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Steamer PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">06PBA01</compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal "/></comp> 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="SECTION_FA07F0308F5843B48FEC03F319945931" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Process</title><fig id="GUID-EADD44EE-07D0-45B8-A493-089D460E6C00" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/></fig><fig id="GUID-807DCED5-35EB-4571-823D-322D5C587717" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-AAF4C152-BE2C-4BB7-89AB-C3C01D7E75BA-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AAF4C152-BE2C-4BB7-89AB-C3C01D7E75BA-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Connection to the print surface platen 
</b> 
</p><fig id="GUID-EA8F9924-C6E0-4362-BACF-E296301C985F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-08BEDEED-87FE-4911-B173-1F61E4447F70-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-08BEDEED-87FE-4911-B173-1F61E4447F70-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Top view and liquid circulation direction of the print surface platen 
</b> 
</p><table id="GUID-9DE7DA46-1049-4251-9AB3-1D1B88BF3B5B" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Startup initialization 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Power on. This process can take up to 30 seconds if the power supply was just turned off. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> After power-on the voltage measurement should be &gt; 50 V and the alarm should not be active. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The temperature control is set to a value of 24 °C 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Degassing runs for 2 minutes (only at first initialization). 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The control valve will be fully open (100%), and the bypass value will be closed (activated). This allows air in the platen and tubes to escape to the chiller reservoir. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If the chiller reservoir temperature is below 24 °C (typical it is 20 °C), the heater will start heating to raise the temperature to 24 °C. 
</p></li></ol></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Wait for the temperature to reach 24 °C (setpoint). 
</p></li></ol></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Stable situation (not printing) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Either the heater or the control valve will be ON, this depends on the environment temperature. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Normally the bypass valve is not active. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Stable situation (printing) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The heaters will be turned OFF, because the cure lamps will be turned on. The cure lamps provide enough heat to keep the platen at the setpoint temperature. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Normally cooling is needed during printing to remove excessive heat from the cure lamps. The control valve will be active (25-100%). In case more cooling is required, the bypass valve will become active (closed) if the control valve is &gt; 80%. The bypass valve becomes inactive (opens) if the control valve drops to &lt; 50%. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Increase setpoint. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">(The platen temperature must be higher) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The control valve is inactive (closed). Bypass valve is inactive (open). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The heater is ON. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the setpoint is almost reached, the heater will reduce power, and the control valve might become active if the temperature becomes too high. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After the setpoint is reached, the platen temperature must be stabilized which can take up to 12 minutes. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decrease setpoint 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">(The platen temperature must be lower) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The heater is OFF. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The control valve is active (25-100%). The bypass valve becomes active (closed) when the control valve is &gt; 80% and becomes inactive when control valve is &lt; 50%. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the setpoint is almost reached, the control valve will reduce power, and the heater might become active if the temperature becomes too low. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After the setpoint is reached, the platen temperature must be stabilized which can take up to 12 minutes. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-3223AA64-D23F-435C-8351-2FDDCEE71EA8.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
